## Automated Token Violation Detection

Run these checks before completing any component work:

```bash
# Find hardcoded hex colors in component and page CSS
grep -rn "#[0-9a-fA-F]\{6\}\|#[0-9a-fA-F]\{3\}" client/components/ client/pages/ --include="*.css"

# Find direct primitive color token usage in component CSS (should never appear)
grep -rn "ld-primitive-color-" client/components/ client/pages/ --include="*.css"

# Find hardcoded pixel values in CSS properties that should use tokens
grep -rn "font-size: [0-9]\|padding: [0-9]\|border-radius: [0-9]" client/components/ client/pages/ --include="*.css"

# Find hardcoded inline colors in TSX files
grep -rn "backgroundColor: '#\|color: '#\|background: '#" client/components/ client/pages/ --include="*.tsx"
```

---

## Enforcement Level

**CRITICAL — NO EXCEPTIONS**

Every component and page, at every PR, must pass the theme compliance check before being merged. Code that uses hardcoded colors or primitive tokens directly must be rejected in review.

